cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with word embeddings and their linguistic properties. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of linear transformations to improve the performance of embedding models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing and the use of embeddings in downstream tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of neural network models for word embeddings. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of embeddings in downstream tasks, some of which may be related to computer vision.
